# Tools

Note all the tools are in python. So in the case you need to do batch processing, you can always consult the python files and write your own script.

## LLM

You always have an LLM at your side to help you with the task. For simple tasks, you could invoke the LLM by running the following command:
```
../py3/Scripts/python ./tools/llm_api.py --prompt "What is the capital of France?"
```

But usually it's a better idea to check the content of the file and use the APIs in the `tools/llm_api.py` file to invoke the LLM if needed.

## Web browser

You could use the `tools/web_scraper.py` file to scrape the web.
```
../py3/Scripts/python ./tools/web_scraper.py --max-concurrent 3 URL1 URL2 URL3
```
This will output the content of the web pages.

## Search engine

You could use the `tools/search_engine.py` file to search the web.
```
../py3/Scripts/python ./tools/search_engine.py "your search keywords"
```
This will output the search results in the following format:
```
URL: https://example.com
Title: This is the title of the search result
Snippet: This is a snippet of the search result
```

## User Specified Lessons

- You have a python venv in ../py3.
- Use relative paths in the code.
- Include info useful for debugging in the program output.
- Read the file before you try to edit it.
- Use LLM to perform flexible text understanding tasks. First test on a few files. After success, make it parallel.
- By default, assume this is under Windows, so use Windows PowerShell not Unix/Linux command.
- Do not include unicode characters.


## Code Style and Structure

- Use docstrings to explain the code.
- Use a single file for a single task.
- Do not use unicode character use reuglar ASCII character
- The file structure is as follows:
```
├── data/           # Input data files
├── output/         # Output files for analysis results including csv files, plots, etc.
├── src/            # Source code files and scripts for different projects
├── tools/          # Tool files
├── docs/           # Latest package docs files

```



